<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB05191</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT MANDATING THE COMMISSION ON HIGHER EDUCATION TO INCLUDE A SUBJECT OF MORO HISTORY, CULTURE AND IDENTITY STUDIES AS AN ELECTIVE IN THE HIGHER EDUCATION CURRICULUM</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Acknowledges that education plays an important role in recognizing the value of interdependence among cultures; Proposes therefore to promote greater appreciation of centuries-long rich historical and cultural heritage among majority of Filipinos by recognizing the rightful place of the Bangsamoro people in the fabric of our national history; Aims to help instill in the consciousness and understanding of the Filipino students the Muslim culture which may possibly eradicate certain biases instilled in the minds of individuals; Emphasizes, among others the positive relations and remembrances in history among the tri-people of Mindanao:  the Christian settlers and their descendants, the Moros or Muslims and the Lumads or indigenous highland tribes.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ALEJANO, GARY C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2017-03-02</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Sy-Alvarado (086 2017-05-08)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HIGHER AND TECHNICAL EDUCATION ON 2017-03-07</td></tr></table>